listitem.para:
Computes the linear optimal LQ full-state gain K  for the state space representation P
\left\{\begin{array}{l}\dot{x}=A x+B u\\z=C x+D u\end{array}\right. \text{ in continuous time or }
  \left\{\begin{array}{l}x^+=A x+B u\\z=C x+D u\end{array}\right.
  \text{ in discrete time.}


And instantaneous cost function in l2-norm:
\left[\begin{array}{ll}x'&u'\end{array}\right]  BigQ  \left[\begin{array}{l}x\\u\end{array}\right] \text{ where }BigQ=\left[\begin{array}{l}C'\\D'\end{array}\right] \left[\begin{array}{ll}C&D\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ll}Q&S'\\S&R\end{array}\right]

refsection.programlisting:
// Form the state space model (assume full state output)
M = 1; m = 0.2; k = 0.1; b = 0.004;
A = [  0     1    0    0
-k/M  -b/M  k/M  b/M
0     0    0    1
k/m  b/m  -k/m  -b/m];
B = [0; 1/M; 0; 0];
C = eye(4,4);
P = syslin("c",A, B, C);
//The compensator weights
Q_xx=diag([15 0 3 0]); //Weights on states
R_uu   = 0.5; //Weight on input
Kc=lqr(P,Q_xx,R_uu);

//form the Plant+compensator system

C=[1 0 0 0  //dy1
0 0 1 0];//dy2
S=C*(P/.(-Kc));
//check system stability
and(real(spec(S.A))<0)
// Check by simulation
dt=0.1;
t=0:dt:30;
u=0.1*rand(t);
y=csim(u,t,S,[1;0;0;0]);
clf;plot(t',y');xlabel(_("time (s)"))
L=legend(["$dy_1$","$dy_2$"]);L.font_size=4;

refsection.scilab:image:
// Form the state space model (assume full state output)
M = 1; m = 0.2; k = 0.1; b = 0.004;
A = [  0     1    0    0
-k/M  -b/M  k/M  b/M
0     0    0    1
k/m  b/m  -k/m  -b/m];
B = [0; 1/M; 0; 0];
C = eye(4,4);
P = syslin("c",A, B, C);
//The compensator weights
Q_xx=diag([15 0 3 0]); //Weights on states
R_uu   = 0.5; //Weight on input
Kc=lqr(P,Q_xx,R_uu);

//form the Plant+compensator system

C=[1 0 0 0  //dy1
0 0 1 0];//dy2
S=C*(P/.(-Kc));
//check system stability
and(real(spec(S.A))<0)
// Check by simulation
dt=0.1;
t=0:dt:30;
u=0.1*rand(t);
y=csim(u,t,S,[1;0;0;0]);
clf;plot(t',y');xlabel(_("time (s)"))
L=legend(["$dy_1$","$dy_2$"]);L.font_size=4;
